<subSubSection id="7DCD21876911027969FFB642BB677928" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="52FFEC40877D1F1BA443BCFFE5D865D1" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FAA85673E99B4B6AB22199049415083E" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="1D4199948F41D8EB07D58A34FF7D2533" authorityName="Bordera &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Piasites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Piasites politus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="politus">
<emphasis id="4AC752C9B0618129A5B1616B2D92E29D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Piasites politus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="1548B3715C75BB466899348C75E90797" authorityName="Seyrig" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Piasites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Piasites" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E55B9655919E8CA03F2BAF2151E6C435" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Piasites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the combination of the following characters: mesoscutum evenly convex, mostly smooth and shiny (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1B59DCB1B6E56CFC0080170DB0F8578E" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Piasites politus sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view (paratype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head, front view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 2 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C); 0.3 mm (D); 0.2 mm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677627" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">9B</figureCitation>
), with very fine punctures on anterior part of median lobe; propodeum from smooth to very shallowly rugulose granulate (Figs 
<figureCitation id="109CE446E30146DE856B8CD2FA49AD27" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Propodeum of Piasites, dorsal view, females (I): A P. carinatus Seyrig B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. politus sp. nov. (paratype) D P. perinetensis sp. nov. (holotype). Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677618" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B74BEB3CC35322670D13DCE7E3D8D517" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Piasites politus sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view (paratype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head, front view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 2 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C); 0.3 mm (D); 0.2 mm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677627" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">9B</figureCitation>
); areolet 0.7-0.9
<normalizedToken id="BC41FB3E4A0799B92B4AC822825A8F86" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as abscissa of vein 2m-cu above bulla (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="30DBD80A1FCCFADF3F7030051E71C8E8" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Piasites politus sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view (paratype) C head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) D head, front view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 2 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C); 0.3 mm (D); 0.2 mm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677627" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">9E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="D1B391BAE026E02893990BB72DABEBBC" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677627" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" start="Figure 9" startId="F9">
